  stimulus_text = 'In the 1970s, the first commercial production of genetically engineered bacteria was developed for use in medicine.  However, the public’s distrust of the new technology has led to a growing awareness of the potential risks of genetic engineering.  As a result, scientists are now focusing on safer and less controversial applications of this technology, such as developing new biofuels and biodegradable plastics.',
